The paper deals with the analysis of greedy algorithms for maximum cardinality matching in graphs and hypergraphs, which falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the limitations of the greedy paradigm and investigates priority algorithms, which are related to the topics of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and graph theory (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper presents analytical results and approximation guarantees, which are relevant to the sub-categories of computational complexity (cs.CC) and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
